The condominium plat may consist of one or more sheets and shall contain at least the following particulars:
The name of the condominium;
A boundary survey of the property described in the declaration showing the location of all buildings on the property and the physical markings at the corners of the property;
Diagrammatic floor plans of each building on the property which show the measured dimensions, floor area, and location of each unit in it. Common elements shall be shown diagrammatically to the extent feasible; and
The elevation, or average elevation in case of minor variances, above sea level, or from a fixed known point, of the upper and lower boundaries of each unit delineated on the condominium plat.
